{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix file descriptor leak in VCD signal dumper initialization\n\n### Summary\nThe VCD signal dumper initialization function `vcd_signal_dumper_init` in `common/utils/LOG/vcd_signal_dumper.c` had a file descriptor leak when pthread creation failed. When `pthread_create` returned an error, the function would set `ouput_vcd = 0` and return without closing the file descriptor that was opened at the beginning of the function. This caused a resource leak that could be triggered when `rr_ul_run` or its downstream functions triggered VCD logging.\n\nThe issue manifested as an accumulation of open file descriptors over time when VCD logging was enabled and pthread creation repeatedly failed. This could eventually lead to the process running out of file descriptors, causing subsequent file operations to fail.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/LOG/vcd_signal_dumper.c`: Added proper file descriptor cleanup in the error path when pthread creation fails in `vcd_signal_dumper_init`.\n\n"
}